The use of a clot-dissolver and aspirin could, alone, save 25000 lives a year in the United States, doctors say. Researchers at the University of Michigan recently determined that some heart attack victims can be released from the hospital as soon as three days after their heart attacks.  Louis, a pioneer in the testing of the clot-dissolvers. With the treatment, the figure dropped to 8 percent. In the most recent report, doctors found that one aspirin tablet and a single dose of a clot-dissolving drug given within 24 hours can dramatically cut the risk of a second fatal heart attack. 